Purpose
This file is the public facade of the library.

Linear intent
1. Re-export the core modules under one stable `Core` namespace so callers do not need to know every internal file name.
2. Re-export the configuration loader under `Config` to keep the external API organized.
3. Re-export the LLM modules under `Llm` so callers can discover the prompt and AegisLM client layers from one place.
4. Re-export the agent modules under `Agents` so users can discover the built-in agents from one place.
5. Re-export the runtime modules under `Runtime`, including the injected services layer.
6. Re-export the orchestration modules under `Orchestration` so the routing layer is accessible without exposing the whole file tree.
7. Provide a single high-level `run` function for the common case.
8. Build the runtime services first so the graph has a ready AegisLM-backed client.
9. Return an explicit error result if the runtime services cannot be created.
10. Build the default registry and the starting context when the services are ready.
11. Start the orchestrator with the initial payload wrapped as `Core_payload.Text`.
12. Return the final payload and context inside a result-aware `Lwt` promise.

